This paper focuses on incorporating monotonic trends in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of interpretability, which is a key aspect of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The proposed approach involves a novel gradient-based point-wise loss function, which is related to optimization and could be categorized under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of deep lattice networks, which are commonly used in "Computer Vision" (cs.CV) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of personalized decisions, which could be related to "Computer Engineering" (cs.CE) and the design of systems that cater to individual needs.
